{"sequence":26,"timestamp":"2026-04-21T23:37:56.821965366Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-1cce7e4f","body":"finding_summary: The branch never implements Part B of the bead: `result` is still tracked in `HEAD`, so `git ls-files -i -c --exclude-standard` still reports it and future checkpoint branches will continue to carry an unrelated `result` diff until the symlink is actually untracked.\nseverity: high\naffected_files:\n- result:1\nremediation_hint: Run `git rm --cached -- result` on this branch and commit that deletion without deleting the working-tree symlink.","dedup_key":"0817de16387e015af8e4ce0a24c90b25f5d3c6595a163cd250bffc137a8eb644","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260421224108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":27,"timestamp":"2026-04-21T23:37:56.853931400Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-116d0ab2","body":"Part B of the bead (untracking `result`) was not performed. `result` is still present in the git index on this branch (`git ls-files result` returns it; `git ls-files -i -c --exclude-standard` on HEAD lists `result`). The only commit on the branch (7518cc15) actually updates the `result` symlink target rather than removing it from the index.\n\nThe bead explicitly states: \"This has two parts. Both must land in this PR.\" It also lists as acceptance criteria:\n- `result` is no longer tracked on `master` (post-merge).\n- `git ls-files -i -c --exclude-standard` on a fresh clone of master prints nothing.\n\nNeither is currently met. Additionally, shipping Part A without Part B has a concrete downstream effect: the next post-merge ralph-burning checkpoint whose parent still tracks `result` will produce a tree that omits `result`, so the checkpoint commit diff shows `result` as a spurious **deletion** rather than the old symlink-target update — the review noise is reshaped rather than eliminated.\n\nRemediation (as specified by the bead): run `git rm --cached -- result` from the repo root and commit the removal on this branch. Do not delete the physical symlink. No other files need untracking — `git ls-files -i -c --exclude-standard` currently returns only `result`.\n\nAffected files: `result` (index entry), repo root.","dedup_key":"bf7371c221c70cc0202a4e154a705c0db546280dafb90dba864568ef18210b8d","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-7-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260421224108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
